kanji.components: 禾: 2-branch tree radical (no. 115) 刀: sword; saber; knife
kanji.koohii1: In the middle ages there where only 2 ways for peasantry to make a profit. one by being a farmer/ 2 to be a mercenary and live by the way of the sword.
kanji.koohii2: 1. Steal a bunch of wheat from a wheat field by cutting it down with your saber. 2. ????? 3. Profit!

kanji_info.image_description: A giant, metallic hand holding a gleaming sword aloft, poised to slice through a field of golden wheat. The wheat is bent and swaying in the wind, representing the 'advantage' gained from wielding the sword. The background is a dramatic sky with lightning bolts, symbolizing the power and potential for 'profit'.

kanji.koohii2: This is Power Mouth/ the most annoying neighbour in the world who always has something to add.

kanji_info.image_description: A playful, cartoon-style image of a giant mouth with teeth made of power bars. It is about to bite into a smaller mouth with a giant plus sign inside, representing the act of 'adding' or 'increasing' something. The scene is bright and colorful, with a cheerful, almost comedic feel.

kanji.koohii1: HELP! Someone´s pinned under this bookshelf and it´s gonna take a lot of muscle to lift it off!
kanji.koohii2: Can you help me move this shelf? I don´t have the muscle to do it alone.

kanji_info.image_description: A powerful, muscular arm reaching out to help a small, struggling figure climb a mountain. The arm is depicted with the symbol for 'power' and the figure is struggling under the weight of a heavy backpack, symbolizing the need for 'assistance'. The mountain represents the challenge being overcome, with a bright sunrise at the peak, signifying hope and success.

kanji.components: 小: small/ insignificant 冖: wa-shaped crown radical (no. 14) 力: power; strength; strong; strain; bear up; exert
kanji.koohii1: Those jocks who always tried to show their muscles in the schoolhouse are now the ones out there doing manual labor jobs while we sit here and learn Japanese. Ha!
kanji.koohii2: At the schoolhouse/ the administration develops the children´s muscles by making them do manual labour.

kanji_info.image_description: A tiny, overworked robot diligently building a towering structure with a giant 'power' symbol on top.  The robot is sweating and exhausted, its gears grinding, representing the 'toil' and 'labor' involved in the task. The structure, however, is beautiful and impressive, signifying the rewards of hard work.

kanji_info.image_description: A fierce warrior, made of raw meat, is battling a giant, weary skeleton with a 'fatigue' symbol on its forehead. The warrior is strong and victorious, with a banner proclaiming 'victory' waving behind it, representing the triumph over adversity.

short_text_with_quiz.text_japanese: ある会社が新しいアプリを開発しています。彼らは、アプリの利用者数を増やし、会社の利益を増加させたいと考えています。開発チームは、アプリの開発に力を入れ、多くの人がプロジェクトに参加しています。開発チームは、開発を助けるために助手も雇い、アプリを成功させるために努力しています。彼らは、この新しいアプリが大きな成功を収め、会社に大きな利益をもたらすと信じています。開発は大変な作業ですが、チームは困難を乗り越え、目標を達成しようと決意しています。
short_text_with_quiz.text_english: A company is developing a new app. They hope to increase the number of users and boost their profits. The development team is working hard, and many people are participating in the project. The team has hired assistants to help with the development process, and they are putting in extra effort to ensure the app is successful. They believe that this new app will be a huge success and bring great benefits to the company. It will be a challenging process, but the team is determined to overcome any obstacles and achieve their goal.

song_lyrics.lyrics_japanese: 私は、他の人を助けて、世界を変えたいと思っています。私は、人々の生活に価値を加え、世界をより良い場所にすることを望んでいます。たとえ小さな親切であっても、大きな影響を与えることができます。私は、どんな状況でも常に他人を助けることに意欲的な人になりたいと思っています。他人を助けることは私を幸せにし、私は社会に貢献していると感じます。小さな親切でも、積み重ねれば大きなものになると信じています。
song_lyrics.lyrics_english_translation: I want to help others and make a difference in the world. I want to add value to people's lives and make the world a better place. Even if it's just a small act of kindness, it can have a big impact. I want to be a person who is always willing to help others, no matter what the situation. Helping others makes me happy, and I feel like I'm making a positive contribution to society. I believe that even small acts of kindness can add up to something big.
